bib_record.title: (n,alpha) reactions on heavy nuclei induced by 14 MeV neutrons

free_txt: n-type surface barrier silicon detector of 15mm
diameter. Energy scale calibration was done using
alphas from Th-C(Bi-212),Th-C (Po-212) and from the
reactions Si-28(n,alpha) and Si-29(n,alpha) in the
ANG-RSL - angle of alpha emission and angular
resolution are given below. Angular resolution was read
from fig.1,P.14 in INR-1401 by compiler and represents
approximately the FWHM of the resolution curve.
The neutron flux was monitored by counting
the recoil protons from a polyethylene foil. Accuracy
of monitoring was better than 2%. Calibration
of the monitor was based on the 847 keV gamma
